  "category": "Uncategorized",
  "description": "Fix Filter Selection Visual Feedback in Gallery and News Components\n\nUpdate the gallery and news filter UI to visually indicate which filter is currently active when users make a selection.\n\nRequirements:\n- Apply active/selected styling to the currently selected filter option\n- Remove active styling from previously selected filter when a new one is chosen\n- Ensure the visual state persists during and after filtering operation\n- Verify active state styling is visible and consistent with design system\n- Test filter selection works correctly for both gallery and news sections\n- Handle initial state (default filter if applicable) with appropriate highlighting\n- Ensure keyboard navigation updates visual state correctly if filters are keyboard-accessible\n\nEdge Cases to Consider:\n- Multiple filters being applied simultaneously (if supported)\n- Filter state when navigating away and returning to the page\n- Filter appearance on page load/refresh with pre-selected filters",
